public class PSComponentDefProcessorProxy
extends PSProcessorProxy

This class is similar to PSComponentProcessorProxy in the way it functions, however it deals with the CMS design objects such as Content Type, Slot, Variant, Workflow definitions etc.

PSComponentDefProcessorProxy

public PSComponentDefProcessorProxy(String processorType,
                                    Object ctx)
                             throws PSCmsException
Creates a proxy for a specific type of processor. Simply delegates to the base class.

Parameters:
processorType - The type of processor for which this class is acting as a proxy. See version of the constructor for more details
ctx - A context object appropriate for the processor type, may be null if the processor does not require one.
Throws:
PSCmsException - If the xml document is not well-formed and conformant to its schema.

load

public Element[] load(String componentType,
                      PSKey[] locators)
               throws PSCmsException
Loads the specified components.

Parameters:
componentType - the type of the loaded components. Never empty or null.
locators - the locators of the loaded components. If null, all objects of the requested type are returned. If any entry is null, an exception is thrown.
Returns:
the specified components, never null, but may be empty.
Throws:
PSCmsException - if an error occurs.
